remarks.format:
## Remarks

`ColorExtensions` bridges the two color representations used in SkiaSharp and HarfBuzzSharp.
`SKColor` uses ARGB order (`0xAARRGGBB`), while `HBColor` uses BGRA order (`0xBBGGRRAA`).
These extension methods convert between them, ensuring the color channel bytes are mapped
correctly in both directions.

## Examples

```csharp
// Convert palette colors from a HarfBuzz face to SKColor
using var face = new HarfBuzzSharp.Face(blob, 0);
HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor[] hbColors = face.GetPaletteColors(0);
SKColor[] skColors = hbColors.ToSKColors();

// Convert an SKColor to HBColor for use with HarfBuzz
SKColor skRed = SKColors.Red;
HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor hbRed = skRed.ToHBColor();
```
